<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="71" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="71">
Sepal lobes and bractlets, completely glabrous. Most similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Leguminosae" genus="Vicia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Vicia taipaica" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="taipaica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Vicia taipaica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs from it by its hastate or lanceolate stipules and subulate bractlets (stipules semi-ovate or lanceolate and bractlets absent in 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Leguminosae" genus="Vicia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Vicia taipaica" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="taipaica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Vicia taipaica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Leguminosae" genus="Vicia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Vicia dichroantha" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dichroantha">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Vicia dichroantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as well, but differs from it by the light yellow or dull orange colour of the corolla and subulate bractlet (yellow, dark yellow or dull orange corolla, marked purple at apex of standard and braclets, absent in 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Leguminosae" genus="Vicia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Vicia dichroantha" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dichroantha">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Vicia dichroantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The new species is restricted to western Jiangxi Province (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Distribution map of Vicia mingyueshanensis (blue dots) and its closest similar species Vicia taipaica (red dots) and Vicia dichroantha (yellow dots)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.187.71960.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/622473" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Vicia mingyueshanensis A, B habitat C habit D the whole plant E pods F pods and seeds G root H inflorescences I leaflets and stipules J bractlet K calyx L tendrils." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.187.71960.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/622474" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">2</figureCitation>
, Table 
<tableCitation captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Detailed comparison of Vicia mingyueshanensis and its two morphologically-similar species." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/15B4F3C5D28588B408C9BEBD6717F3EC" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" tableUuid="15B4F3C5D28588B408C9BEBD6717F3EC">1</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
